commit 97eeb10ebbb190a12bb74e0520451ebbcd8d723c
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 14:08:57 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(per-page-content): migrate evergreen routes to getPage; delete per-page flat translation keys
    
    Migrate the evergreen routes (about, faq, give, contact, volunteer, home) to
    read their copy from the per-Page objects via Content.getPage(id), projected to
    the current locale at the boundary, and delete the per-page flat translation
    keys that now have a typed home (about.*, faq.*, give.* copy, contact/volunteer
    page copy, and home-evergreen main.* keys). UI-chrome keys (nav, buttons,
    form labels) stay in Translations.
    
    - app/lib/content/pages/project.ts: per-locale boundary projection (toAboutView
      / toFaqView / toGiveView / toContactView / toVolunteerView / toHomeView +
      toRichText), the toConference analogue for Pages so React never sees the
      bilingual Text or an Option (boundary-discipline, small-interface-deep-impl).
    - app/ui/rich-text.tsx: the single closed-token RichText renderer (text/bold/
      link), turning a \n\n in a run back into <br/><br/> so the FAQ/contact copy
      renders identically to the deleted flat keys.
    - Routes gain thin loaders reading getPage and .map over the page lists (faq's
      three hand-written QuestionLayout blocks collapse to one .map).
    - defaults.ts: the FAQ default answers carry the full faithful copy + \n\n
      breaks so the migrated route renders at parity.
    
    Conscious styling deltas (the 5.1 schemas, already committed, do not model
    these): the home tagline loses its gradient-underlined movement/for words and
    the join subtitle loses its {{br}} break; give/volunteer titles render plain
    (no italic movement). Copy substance is identical EN+FR.
    
    Tests: project.test.ts (per-locale projection + link-href carry-through +
    \n\n preserved); rich-text.test.tsx (token->DOM, \n\n -> <br/><br/>).

